@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "01" where you
want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files
or Libraries are needed.

NOTE: I am not sure of this game's 'behaviour' on a stock 68000
      Amiga. For now, until somebody confirms that '01' runs fine
      on a 68000 machine, this game will require an Amiga with a
      68020 or faster processor... sorry!

                             How to play?

  The game is played on a 8 by 8 spaces board, which contains a
number of fixed coloured '0's and '1's. A 'Status' indicator,
located at the right of the game board, shows the number of rows
and columns that are completed. When the number gets to 16/16, the
game is completed.

  To play, click on any tile which contains a small dot, a '0' or
a '1' (except on the coloured numbers). If the clicked position is
a dot, it will change to a '0', otherwise, the state of the number
will change from a '0' to a '1' and vice versa...

  Have fun!

OPTIONS
-------

  New Game: To restart the game.

  Colour:   To change the colour of the fixed '0's and '1's.

  You can quit the game by clicking on the game window's close
button or by pressing on the 'Esc' key.

